  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Stroke is the third common cause of adult disability in dveloped countries. Early
      identification of the potential for motor recovery is important to avoid 'learned disuse' and
      to initiate appropriate therapy with achievable goals. The current cohort study focuses on
      those patients with SAFE &lt;8 and using motor evoked potentials (MEPs) to improve on
      prognostication of upper limb motor recovery among subacute stroke patients in a local stroke
      population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
